ABB links with Kawasaki Heavy Industries in Kobe venture 
Asea Brown Boveri has linked with Kawasaki Heavy Industries to
establish a joint venture, Nippon Power Systems, at Kobe.
ABB, in a statement on Monday, said that it would hold 51 percent of
the new company and Kawasaki 49 percent.
The new venture would supply factories and power stations in Asia with
steam turbines built by ABB.
The two companies are already associated in Japan Gas Turbines KK.
